            <title>[THRIFT-4] Default values of non-primitive types aren&apos;t copied on new object creation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you create a Thrift type that has a default value for a field, and the default value is non-primitive (a hash, thrift object, array, etc), then all instances of that class share the same default object instead of copies of that object.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
